snippet.textDisplay: The switching could have definitely been done with mosfets. Using low voltage mosfets with an RDS(on) of 0.5mOhms would have each mosfet producing 5w of heat at 100A, which could have almost been done passively. Then put 10 or more in parallel to get the current rating you need. The gate capacitance would be huge, but you're not trying to use pwm so ultra fast switching times are not necessary.
snippet.textOriginal: The switching could have definitely been done with mosfets. Using low voltage mosfets with an RDS(on) of 0.5mOhms would have each mosfet producing 5w of heat at 100A, which could have almost been done passively. Then put 10 or more in parallel to get the current rating you need. The gate capacitance would be huge, but you're not trying to use pwm so ultra fast switching times are not necessary.
